caseText:"<p>Bhatia &amp; Sharma LLP (BS LLP) is an accounting firm in form of limited liability partnership with 20+ branches across India, in all major cities. BS LLP offers to its customer services in accountancy, assurance, tax consultancy, business advisory services. Due to the economic slowdown in the country, large numbers of business are entering into either internal/ external reconstruction; as a result, advisory services are in huge demand. BS started its business advisory domain service just recently over the past one year. The industry of accounting practices in India is mature, despite some of statues enforced recently. Each domain of service is under the charge of a team of partners. They have clearly demarcated work assignments within themselves.</p> <p>As part of performance analysis, at BS LLP; partners for each service domain collectively meet with top officers, on monthly basis. Following performance related data (belong to latest financial year) was considered in one of recent conducted partner meeting.</p> <table> <tbody> <tr> <th>Particulars for BS LLP</th> <th>Accounting</th> <th>Audits</th> <th>Tax Consultancy</th> <th>Business Advisory</th> </tr> <tr> <td>Revenue (In ` Crores)</td> <td>700</td> <td>823</td> <td>175</td> <td>120</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Revenue (In ` Crores)</td> <td>2%</td> <td>6%</td> <td>10%</td> <td>18%</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Net profit ratio</td> <td>5%</td> <td>3%</td> <td>7%</td> <td>12%</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Revenue (In ` Crores) of Accounting Industry as whole</td> <td>3500</td> <td>7210</td> <td>1835</td> <td>300</td> </tr> </tbody> </table> <p>For the coming year, the partners have set an across the board 10% growth of revenue target over previous year. This is applicable to all the segments.</p> <p>Remuneration Structure at BS LLP</p> <ul> <li>Partners are getting fixed contractual payment apart from a variable pay. Each partner will be compensated based on the revenue they generate in their domain service.</li> <li>Non&ndash;Partners are getting fixed salary apart from variable pay depending upon rating in their performance appraisal that they have with their reporting seniors The rating will take into consideration their individual performance, contribution to the team, their skill sets and overall potential for future contribution to the firm. However, in addition to individual and team performance the variable pay is also dependent on the firm&rsquo;s financial performance during the year. There have been instances when a good performer who is part of a well performing team did not any significant variable pay on account of the firm not meeting its profit targets.</li> <li>HR team holds periodic meetings to explain the remuneration structure to the employees.</li> </ul> <p>Client Relation Officer who is working parallel to marketing team, first time participated in monthly performance evaluation meeting and presented following data which contain rating from clients of BS LLP. It is decided that these rating will also be added in performance matrix/ table stated above</p> <table> <tbody> <tr> <th>Particulars for BS LLP</th> <th>Accounting</th> <th>Audits</th> <th>Tax Consultancy</th> <th>Business Advisory</th> </tr> <tr> <td>Customer Ratings (higher the better) on a scale of 5</td> <td>3.2</td> <td>2.9</td> <td>3.4</td> <td>4.6</td> </tr> </tbody> </table> ",    
